// The published modules in this repository, wired together for local
// development.
//
// Each provider `require`s a published version of the root module. Without this
// workspace they would compile against that published version even here, so a
// breaking change to the root would pass CI while silently breaking every
// provider. The workspace overrides that requirement with the working tree.
//
// It is committed so CI uses it too, and it is ignored entirely when someone
// depends on any of these modules. To reproduce a consumer's build, set
// GOWORK=off.
//
// The modules under examples/ are deliberately absent. They are never published
// or tagged, and they wire themselves to the working tree with their own
// `replace` directives so each one stays a copy-pasteable, self-contained
// program. No published module here carries a `replace`.
//
// Releasing bumps each provider's `require` to the new root tag; see
// CONTRIBUTING.md / AGENTS.md.

go 1.24

use (
	.
	./msg91
	./sns
	./twilio
	./vonage
)
